Useful code and Notes

grep -H "[A-Za-z0-9]" *.csv | cut -d, -f1-5 | sed "s|:|,|" > all.csv --> grepped all files in one directory, merged them into one and kept the filenames as indicatior

awk '{sub(/[^,]*/,"");sub(/,/,"")} 1'  --> delete first column in csv

wc -l --> numbers of rows of csv

tr ' ' ',' <lenght_corrected_lv_romance_off_diagonal.csv > length.csv --> replace space with comma

